    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="303" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Thayer</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 13, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received and have read with much
                            interest your despatch of the 29th of June, (No. 3,) announcing your
                            arrival in Egypt, and giving an account of your reception by the
                            viceroy. Your remarks on that occasion, as well as your conduct
                            throughout the imposing ceremonial, are approved, and the friendly
                            feeling towards the United States manifested by his highness in your
                            interview with him, and subsequently by his minister of foreign affairs,
                            and by the consuls general representing other nations in Egypt, is very
                            gratifying.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William S. Thayer</hi>, Esq.,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Consul General of the United States, Alexandria,
                                    Egypt</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
